article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Micah Thomas scored 15 points as Northwestern State beat Incarnate Word 72-70 on Thursday night. Thomas shot 4 for 7 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 6 of 7 from the free-throw line for the Demons (4-5, 1-0 Southland Conference). Landyn Jumawan shot 5 for 6, including 4 for 4 from beyond the arc to add 14 points. Jon Sanders had 12 points and shot 4 for 9, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc. The Cardinals (4-4, 0-1) were led by Davion Bailey, who recorded 22 points and seven rebounds. Dylan Hayman added 19 points for Incarnate Word. Jalin Anderson finished with 11 points and eight assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
